@modus:root:/ 21> help *report_fault_effects*
Commands:
    report_fault_effects:

    report_fault_effects is used to perform simulation on the specified 
    list of faults and reports the fault effects. 


report_fault_effects:

 [-H]                                  Advanced help text
 [-h]                                  Help text
 [-v]                                  Verbose Output
 [-w]                                  Wait for Files to free if in use
 [-ALTFAULT <string>]                  Alternate Fault Model Name
 [-EXPERIMENT <string>]                Input experiment name
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
 [-TB_USE_NETNAMES yes|no] (yes)       Use net names instead of pin names in Modus messages
  -TESTMODE <string>                   Test Mode Name
  -WORKDIR <string>                    Working Directory
 [-aliascheck no|yes] (no)             Check for fault aliasing on designs with XOR compression
 [-checkpoint <integer 0 or greater>] (Conditional Default) Checkpoint Interval in minutes (approximate)
 [-choppers safe|risky] (Conditional Default) Clock Chopper Simulation
 [-comparemeasures no|yes] (no)        Compare PO Measures
 [-constraintcheck no|yes] (no)        Detect Run-Time Constraint Violations.
 [-contentionreport soft|hard|all|none] (none) Type of Three-state Contention to Report
 [-coreinstance <string>]              specify active migrated core instance name or Id for Hierarchal Test run.
 [-countxcaptureswitches half|no|yes] (half) Count X transitions as switching activity
 [-delaymode zero|unit] (Conditional Default) Delay Mode for Simulation
  -faultinjectionfile <infilename>     Specify the file name containing the list of faults for fault simulation.
 [-faultsperpass <string>] (0)         Number of Faults per Pass
 [-fmosc <integer>]                    Fault Machine Oscillation Detection Threshold
 [-gmosc <integer 0 to 64000>] (Conditional Default) Good Machine Oscillation Detection Threshold
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-keepers safe|risky|no] (Conditional Default) Keeper Device Simulation
 [-latchsimulation optimistic|pessimistic] (Conditional Default) Sim Latch/Flip-flop Output to X when Clock at X
 [-lotwaferheader yes|no] (Conditional Default) Adds the header containing lot, wafer details for the set of failures in a device.
 [-machinesize <integer>] (25000)      Maximum Fault Machine Size
 [-maxcputime <decimal 0.01 or greater>] Maximum CPU Minutes (approximate)
 [-maxelapsedtime <decimal 0.01 or greater>] Maximum Elapsed Minutes (approximate)
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-outputdirectoryname <outdir>]       Output directory name to write out the failure files.
 [-outputfilename <outfilename>] (Conditional Default) Output file name to write out the fault effects.
 [-outputscriptname <outfilename>|no] (run_logic_diagnostics.tcl) Specify the name of the Tcl script file containing the logic diagnostics flow for the faults injected by this command.
 [-propxignore no|yes] (Conditional Default) Propagate X to Downstream Logic from Ignored Location
 [-quiet no|yes] (no)                  Print Fewer Messages
 [-ramsize all|<integer>:] (Conditional Default) RAM Address Space Size
 [-ramtest no|yes] (Conditional Default) ramtest,arraytest
 [-restart yes|no]                     Restart from Checkpoint
 [-testrange all|<odometerRange>[,all|<odometerRange>]...] Select Range of Tests
 [-useatpgsimoptions no|yes] (no)      Use Simulation Options from Modus
 [-writemisrfails 1pass|2pass|1passserial] (1pass) This is valid only for OPMISR test modes. Enables the writing of failures in special OPMISR mode.
 [-xwidth <integer>]                   Delay Uncertainty for PI changes

